Description: Fragment of oval handle from a Thasian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine micaceous light red-brown. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and star and pilos symbol.
Production date: 250BC-200BC (M. Debidour, 'En classant les timbres thasiennes', BCH suppl. XIII, Paris 1986, 330-334.)
Curator's comments: Name Philonides. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 32, 4. From same die as Tzochev, C, The Athenian Agoraxxxvii 170, no. 337c.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0034)
